
Function: ZEROP

Syntax:   (ZEROP arg1)

 arg1 (required, evaluated) - a number.

Returns:

 T if arg1 is numerically zero, else NIL.

Processing:

Errors signaled:

 Non-numeric argument.

Notes:

 No errors are detected in compiled code; results are unpredictable
 if an invalid argument is passed.

Examples:

 (ZEROP 0)         ==> T
 (ZEROP 1)         ==> NIL
 (ZEROP -1)        ==> NIL
 (ZEROP 0.0)       ==> T
 (ZEROP -0.0)      ==> T
 (ZEROP 0.0001)    ==> NIL
 (ZEROP 0.0F0)     ==> T
 (ZEROP -0.0F0)    ==> T
 (ZEROP 0.0001F0)  ==> NIL

